node.title: Man arrested after firing gun, pointing it at police in Auckland
node.description: A man has been arrested after allegedly pointing a gun at police and firing it three times at random in west Auckland.
node.content:
["A man has been arrested after allegedly pointing a gun at police and firing it three times at random in west Auckland.", "", "
(File photo). Photo: RNZ / Marika Khabazi
", "Officers and the armed offenders squad were called a property in Cherry Tree Place in Massey early this morning.", "Police say no-one was hurt when the man fired the gun.", "The 28-year-old is due to appear in the Waitākere District Court today."]
